    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1865-11-03T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1865-11-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="457"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d457">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                        Bigelow</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 297.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State,</hi>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1865-11-03">
                            <hi rend="italic">November</hi> 3, 1865.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> I am directed by the President to request you to
                    ask the serious attention of the French government to the military proceedings
                    in Mexico, by which native Mexicans taken captive while adhering in war to their
                    own republican government are denied rights which the law of nations invariably
                    accords to prisoners of war.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWAED.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">John Bigelow,</hi> Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c.,
                            &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
